{"word":"περιπατέω","slug":"περιπατέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>περιπατέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:περίπατος'><el>περίπατος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to walk up and down, to walk about</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: generally, <i>to walk</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to walk</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>live</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}